      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "### Request audit contract\nEvery `litellm_request` span becomes one log line in the Loki stream `{service_name=\"aigw-requests\"}`. Each line carries `aigw.user.id` (stable subject UUID), `aigw.user.name` (readable identity: chat end user, portal username, or key alias — attribution only, never an authorization record), `aigw.enduser.id`, `aigw.project.id`, `aigw.api_key.id` (SHA-256 fingerprint only), `aigw.request.id`, the model/token/cost fields, and the approved `gen_ai.input.messages` / `gen_ai.output.messages` content; `| logfmt` exposes them as `aigw_user_id`-style fields (Logs Drilldown filters work the same way). `aigw_user_name` and `aigw_project_id` are also Loki stream labels — use the User/Project dropdowns above to filter every panel. Raw authorization, API keys, request headers, email, IP, and unfiltered LiteLLM auth metadata are removed before any export. Prompt content is sensitive and this dashboard is intentionally ADM-only.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.5",
      "title": "How to inspect a request",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "loki"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never"
          },
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "sum"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom",
          "showLegend": true
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.5",
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "loki"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (aigw_user_name) (count_over_time({service_name=\"aigw-requests\", aigw_user_name=~\"$user\", aigw_project_id=~\"$project\"} | logfmt [$__auto]))",
          "queryType": "range",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Requests by User",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
